<subSubSection lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="419" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,1885,2018]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1885,1910]" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The species 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[438,543,1886,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solari">
<emphasis box="[438,543,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">C. solari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[908,1000,1886,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[908,1000,1886,1910]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Colletes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the following diagnostic characters: compound eyes are strongly emarginate, more conspicuously so in the male (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1222,1921,1946]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) and T2–T5 with a slight golden iridescence when backlit. In contrast with C. 
<emphasis box="[811,941,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">bombiformi</emphasis>
s or C. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[1023,1135,1959,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigerrima">
<emphasis box="[1023,1135,1959,1982]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">nigerrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the clypeus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[1312,1410,1958,1982]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solari">
<emphasis box="[1312,1331,1958,1981]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1345,1410,1958,1982]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">solari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is less projected and the discal area is not depressed (
<figureCitation box="[754,842,1993,2018]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). In addition, the following apomorphies define 
<emphasis box="[1410,1429,1994,2017]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="418">C</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,429]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ayala" authorityYear="2017" box="[151,216,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solari">
<emphasis box="[151,216,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">solari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: two apical processes on both sides of the distal margin of clypeus (more conspicuous on males); malar area and clypeus longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[494,577,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
); a pad-shaped elevation on the anterior margin of the mesoscutum (stronger in males, 
<figureCitation box="[258,340,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
), which is divided by the mesoscutal median line; integument on pad-shaped projection is dull and with faint and small reticulate striae; all apical bands of terga slim and golden in the female and whitish in the male (
<figureCitation box="[159,302,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Figs. 50, 51</figureCitation>
); thick striae on the posterior area of the propodeal triangle; the frons and area near the antennal sockets with thick striae with coarse appearance; all femora are dilated, especially in males (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1324,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 50 – 56" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1830,1853]" captionTargetBox="[221,1358,515,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[192,1395,481,1810]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 50 – 56. Colletes solari Balboa &amp; Ayala sp. n. 50 — female holotype: habitus, lateral view; 51 — male allotype: habitus, lateral view; 52 — male paratype: detail of anterior margin of scutum; 53 — male paratype: head; 54 — male allotype: S 7; 55 — male allotype: S 8; 56 — male allotype: genital capsule." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051947/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); anterior femur with whitish pubescence in the proximal half and black hairs in the distal half; males with a ridge-shaped elevation on the frons below the median ocellus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
